[3] Washington State (Skagit County)
Date: Wed 6 Jun 2012
Source: KAPS radio [edited]
http://www.kapsradio.com/kaps-radio-660am-news-headlines/skagit-county-has-the-highest-rate-of-pertussis/


The Washington State Department of Health says Skagit County now has 433 confirmed cases of whooping cough or pertussis, the most in state by a wide margin. In new numbers released yesterday, 5 Jun 2012, health officials say Skagit County also has the highest rate of pertussis per 100 000 residents at 363.

