[6] Utah (Utah County)
Date: Wed 6 Jun 2012
Source: Daily Herald [edited]
http://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/whooping-cough-cases-continue-to-rise-in-utah-county/article_a1febe87-378d-5bb6-b41e-1a4c39e3fed5.html


The Utah County Health Department is continuing to investigate new cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, every week. In 2012, 96 cases have been reported throughout the county, which is more than the cases recorded in 2009 and 2010 combined.

In 2011, the health department reported 157 cases of whooping cough, the highest number of cases in Utah County in more than 5 years and Dr Joseph Miner, executive director of the Utah County Health Department, said the county is on track to pass that number in 2012.

[byline: Paige Fieldsted]

