[7] Florida (Hillsborough County)
Date: Sat 2 Jun 2012
Source: The Ledger, Tampa Bay Times report [edited]
http://www.theledger.com/article/20120602/NEWS/120609903/1374


An outbreak of whooping cough in Hillsborough County has struck 10 schools, 9 public and 1 private. Now health officials worry that summer camps, outings, and family vacations may allow the illness, also known as pertussis, to spread even more widely. "Kids will be fanning out to various churches, camps, and community centers, which increases the opportunity to spread pertussis and the number of people who will be exposed," said Warren McDougle, epidemiology program manager for the Hillsborough County Health Department. "The school year ending isn't necessarily going to bring us relief from this outbreak."

So far in 2012, Hillsborough County has seen about 40 cases. In 2011, Hillsborough reported just 2 cases between January and June.

[byline: Irene Maher]

