[8] Wisconsin (Pierce County)
Date: Fri 1 Jun 2012
Source: River Falls Journal [edited]
http://www.riverfallsjournal.com/event/article/id/102197/


The River Falls School District sent notification to all parents in the district on Fri 1 Jun 2012, saying the Pierce County Health Department has confirmed 3 cases of pertussis, commonly known as whooping cough, in students from 3 local schools: Rocky Branch Elementary, Meyer Middle, and the high school.

The message says, "We are making all parent/guardians in the School District aware of this confirmation and also want to share information with you regarding this contagious disease and its symptoms."

