[10] Oregon
Date: Thu 31 May 2012
Source: Examiner [edited]
http://www.examiner.com/article/oregon-pertussis-cases-dramatically-higher-2012


Much of the country is experiencing increases in pertussis, or whooping cough so far this year [2012] and the Northwest of the country has been hit exceptionally hard.

In Oregon, health officials reported that as of 29 May 2012, there have been 294 reported pertussis cases. This number dwarfs the 112 cases reported during the same timeframe in 2011.

The Oregon Health Authority says the ages of 2012 pertussis cases range from 8 days to 58 years; the median age is 8 years. There have been 11 infants hospitalized; 10 are 3 months old or younger.

[byline: Robert Herriman]

