[12] New York (Niagara County)
Date: Fri 8 Jun 2012
Source: WGRZ [edited]
http://www.wgrz.com/news/article/170808/1/Niagara-County-Report-Increase-in-Pertussis-Cases


Officials at the Niagara County Department of Health say several cases of pertussis have been reported recently in their county. They say 15 cases have been medically diagnosed since January 2012 to now, compared to 11 cases for the entire year in 2011.

Affected individuals range in age from 65 years to 2 months, with a predominance of cases in school-age children. None of the sick had to be hospitalized and all received treatment at home.

